name: Vintage Old Maid Cards Mounted - Circus Edition
description:
These cards are just fabulous! They were produced by the Ed-U-Card company in the USA in the late 1950s and into the early 1960s. The colours and illustrations are glorious (although somewhat male-centric) and features such characters as Rodney Ringmaster, Swingin' Sam, Enormous Norma and many more.

This picture features nine original cards mounted on an archival-quality acid-free mat. It measures approximately 34cm x 44cm.

name: Red buckle brooch # 2

name: Hello there! Lovely set of four notecards #1
description:
Sometimes there just isn't a lot to say... Well these postcard/notecards are just perfect for that! 

This set of four comes with envelopes - of course - and are posted in a cellophane sleeve for protection. They make a lovely little gift too. Just pop a bit of ribbon or jute around them and there you go!
